<component id="ID_exp_title">
  <text><![CDATA[Placing All Hosts in One Local Network Segment]]></text> 
</component>
<component id="ID_expText1">
  <text><![CDATA[<p align="left">Advantages:<UL><li>Appropriate for simpler networks</LI><li>Less complexity and lower network cost</LI><li>Allows devices to be "seen" by other devices</LI><li>Faster data transfer - more direct communication</LI><li>Ease of device access</LI></UL><br/>Disadvantages:<br/><UL><LI>All hosts are in one broadcast domain which causes more traffic on the segment and may slow network performance </LI><br />]]></text> 
</component>
<component id="ID_exp_title2">
  <text><![CDATA[Placing Hosts in Remote Network Segments]]></text> 
</component>
<component id="ID_expText2">
  <text><![CDATA[<p align="left">Advantages:<UL><li>More appropriate for larger, more complex networks</LI><li>Splits up broadcast domains and decreases traffic</LI><li>Can improve performance on each segment</LI><li>Makes the machines invisible to those on other local network segments</LI><li>Can provide increased security</LI><li>Can improve network organization</LI></UL><br />Disadvantages:<UL><LI>Requires the use of routing (distribution layer)<li>Router can slow traffic between segments<li>More complexity and expense (requires router)</LI>]]></text> 
</component>

<component id="ID_instructions"><text><![CDATA[<p align="left"><b>Roll over each LAN topology to view the advantages and disadvantages of maintaining a single local network or multiple local networks.</b></p>]]></text> 
</component>

